    <item>
      <title>Corona Trends</title>
      <link>https://gerardbriscoe.github.io/portfolio/coronatrends/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 01 Jan 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://gerardbriscoe.github.io/portfolio/coronatrends/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;btn btn-outline-primary my-1&#34; href=&#34;https://coronatrends.github.io&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Project Site&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;















&lt;figure  &gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Screenshot&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /portfolio/coronatrends/sample_huc2f7902edb08eaa78faddd419e3e409e_241324_edbded25caa1b70f4b86da85c08be0d1.webp 400w,
               /portfolio/coronatrends/sample_huc2f7902edb08eaa78faddd419e3e409e_241324_d5dbbc8ba70a799071bcc7e963eb4286.webp 760w,
               /portfolio/coronatrends/sample_huc2f7902edb08eaa78faddd419e3e409e_241324_1200x1200_fit_q75_h2_lanczos_3.webp 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://gerardbriscoe.github.io/portfolio/coronatrends/sample_huc2f7902edb08eaa78faddd419e3e409e_241324_edbded25caa1b70f4b86da85c08be0d1.webp&#34;
               width=&#34;760&#34;
               height=&#34;454&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a lack of graphs focusing on cities in the Covid pandemic, especially in showing their current and trending situation. So, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.rca.ac.uk/research-innovation/research-centres/helen-hamlyn-centre/research-projects/2018-projects/global-healthcare-index/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;past research&lt;/a&gt;, on identifying key cities for creating global indices, was used to include a selection of 7 cities per region based upon Loughborough Universityâ€™s &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.lboro.ac.uk/gawc/world2018link.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;City Link Classification&lt;/a&gt; (connectivity), nation diversity, as well as city, national and regional contributions to Global Domestic Product (GDP).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Modified version of the graph created by &lt;a href=&#34;https://aatishb.com/covidtrends/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Aatish Bhatia&lt;/a&gt; in collaboration with &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/user/minutephysics&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Minute Physics&lt;/a&gt;. This graph was chosen as it effectively represents &lt;strong&gt;exponential growth&lt;/strong&gt; trends, which is perhaps the most &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kas0tIxDvrg&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;challenging aspect of pandemics&lt;/a&gt;. The short explainer video is a clip from Minute Physics &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=54XLXg4fYsc&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;explainer video&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>What the Hell?</title>
      <link>https://gerardbriscoe.github.io/portfolio/wth/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 01 Jan 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://gerardbriscoe.github.io/portfolio/wth/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;btn btn-outline-primary btn-page-header&#34; href=&#34;https://gerardbriscoe.github.io/wth&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Project Site&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;















&lt;figure  &gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Prototype&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /portfolio/wth/sample_huc6c757ce29f9323e548d698b1c0ec1d5_33790_16cf0d2bdbee03cfddda917598bedcf7.webp 400w,
               /portfolio/wth/sample_huc6c757ce29f9323e548d698b1c0ec1d5_33790_e324250afa3703a82a6e2a8745222d69.webp 760w,
               /portfolio/wth/sample_huc6c757ce29f9323e548d698b1c0ec1d5_33790_1200x1200_fit_q75_h2_lanczos_3.webp 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://gerardbriscoe.github.io/portfolio/wth/sample_huc6c757ce29f9323e548d698b1c0ec1d5_33790_16cf0d2bdbee03cfddda917598bedcf7.webp&#34;
               width=&#34;700&#34;
               height=&#34;508&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I was working in projects concerning ethical consumers, including the potential for blockchains to potentially demonstrate the provenance of products. I noted that perhaps more simply what was required was knowledge of brand ownership, rather than the full history of a product&amp;rsquo;s origin, because one ultimately has to believe the information that would be placed on a blockchain. However, with current corporate culture it can be unclear who owns a given brand, and so whether the owner&amp;rsquo;s values are consistent with the brand&amp;rsquo;s values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I created a tool to determine the ownership of a brand. I wanted as self-sustaining a solution as far as possible, so rather than build a complex server to handle queries, I looked for a primarily client-side solution. I realised I needed a suitable data source, such as &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.wikipedia.org&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Wikipedia&lt;/a&gt;, and a suitable way to access information (API) as client-side data scraping would not be effective. I discovered &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.dbpedia.org&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;DBpedia&lt;/a&gt; which makes Wikipedia information available in a database format, such that queries can be submitted in the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.w3.org/TR/sparql11-query/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;SPARQL&lt;/a&gt; query language. I wanted a &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.w3schools.com/html/html_responsive.asp&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;responsive web design&lt;/a&gt; that would provide a web app, as well as a website. I considered that the &lt;a href=&#34;http://getskeleton.com&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Skeleton&lt;/a&gt; CSS library would be sufficient for my needs of building a prototype interface.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;















&lt;figure  &gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Example GUI To Show Ownership Hierarchy&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /portfolio/wth/gui_hu29de4adea43818c2f358ce9560aa7ce5_406257_ee39e5dfff67ea826737119feca7cb76.webp 400w,
               /portfolio/wth/gui_hu29de4adea43818c2f358ce9560aa7ce5_406257_5034614ad198e48d5b50e05db8b3811f.webp 760w,
               /portfolio/wth/gui_hu29de4adea43818c2f358ce9560aa7ce5_406257_1200x1200_fit_q75_h2_lanczos_3.webp 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://gerardbriscoe.github.io/portfolio/wth/gui_hu29de4adea43818c2f358ce9560aa7ce5_406257_ee39e5dfff67ea826737119feca7cb76.webp&#34;
               width=&#34;760&#34;
               height=&#34;757&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I subsequently considered creating a more graphical interface, which could show the hierarchy of ownership. I first made use of &lt;a href=&#34;https://d3js.org&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;D3&lt;/a&gt;, before concluding it would probably be better to make a native app.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Touchscreen Thimbles</title>
      <link>https://gerardbriscoe.github.io/portfolio/touchscreenthimbles/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 01 Jan 2016 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://gerardbriscoe.github.io/portfolio/touchscreenthimbles/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;















&lt;figure  &gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /portfolio/touchscreenthimbles/sketch_hu70facba2c1e0cf04bec9bf88d07d64f2_184499_887151671e097caf11ea7df6440a90c8.webp 400w,
               /portfolio/touchscreenthimbles/sketch_hu70facba2c1e0cf04bec9bf88d07d64f2_184499_8d4d535e071e43ead272587c17951639.webp 760w,
               /portfolio/touchscreenthimbles/sketch_hu70facba2c1e0cf04bec9bf88d07d64f2_184499_1200x1200_fit_q75_h2_lanczos_3.webp 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://gerardbriscoe.github.io/portfolio/touchscreenthimbles/sketch_hu70facba2c1e0cf04bec9bf88d07d64f2_184499_887151671e097caf11ea7df6440a90c8.webp&#34;
               width=&#34;760&#34;
               height=&#34;603&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are interested in the challenge that the ever-increasing use of capacitive touchscreens represent. This is because they rely on the electrical properties of the human skin, which changes over time, often becoming less conductive with age. So, we consider the potentially increasing problem this would represent, as a frame from which to better understand the design requirements for developing solutions. Conscious of the need to retain a sense of touch, rather than a stylus with a conductive tip or gloves with conductive finger tips, we then propose suitable thimbles for touchscreens. We conceptualised a touchscreen thimble to be worn on the body that would maintain a sense of touch. So a pros-palliare, rather than a prosthesis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;















&lt;figure  &gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /portfolio/touchscreenthimbles/design_huac23f108dd9350c2c47c7e66e57f88f6_1107032_cd7c2ee5889ccf4a0af9c867ed3ecf14.webp 400w,
               /portfolio/touchscreenthimbles/design_huac23f108dd9350c2c47c7e66e57f88f6_1107032_021402016bc7c1bdf6e9890e375fe3ce.webp 760w,
               /portfolio/touchscreenthimbles/design_huac23f108dd9350c2c47c7e66e57f88f6_1107032_1200x1200_fit_q75_h2_lanczos_3.webp 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://gerardbriscoe.github.io/portfolio/touchscreenthimbles/design_huac23f108dd9350c2c47c7e66e57f88f6_1107032_cd7c2ee5889ccf4a0af9c867ed3ecf14.webp&#34;
               width=&#34;760&#34;
               height=&#34;353&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The design of the touchscreen thimble consists of two essential parts, a rigid cylindrical base, and a thin conductive fabric for the finger tip. Developing a proof of concept prototype, with Jeroen Blom, addressing the limitations we observed with existing approaches.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;















&lt;figure  &gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /portfolio/touchscreenthimbles/prototype_hu8a13418ac36946d884b2125a85f6f02f_323767_78b1edd9f170e8774b13be9f65618e5d.webp 400w,
               /portfolio/touchscreenthimbles/prototype_hu8a13418ac36946d884b2125a85f6f02f_323767_5ddea60651a82dde523dcde4bb59e46c.webp 760w,
               /portfolio/touchscreenthimbles/prototype_hu8a13418ac36946d884b2125a85f6f02f_323767_1200x1200_fit_q75_h2_lanczos.webp 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://gerardbriscoe.github.io/portfolio/touchscreenthimbles/prototype_hu8a13418ac36946d884b2125a85f6f02f_323767_78b1edd9f170e8774b13be9f65618e5d.webp&#34;
               width=&#34;760&#34;
               height=&#34;507&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The front thimble showing a rigid base made from antler combined with a grey conductive fabric tip.&lt;/p&gt;
